ate(false);\nconst [optimisticModel, setOptimisticModel] = useState<string | null>(null);\n```\n\nThe outside-click handler mirrors the existing session dropdown pattern using `modelRef`.\n\n### Data Fetching\n\nModels are fetched lazily — only when the popover is first opened:\n\n```\nmodelOpen becomes true\n  → useEffect fires (dependency: [modelOpen])\n  → if already loaded, skip\n  → calls listModels({ available: true })\n  → stores result in `models` state\n```\n\nClient-side filtering: `models.filter(m => (m.provider + \" \" + m.model).includes(modelSearch))` on every keystroke.\n\n### Popover UI\n\nMatches the session dropdown's visual style:\n\n```\nabsolute right-0 top-full mt-1\nw-80\nbg-surface border border-border-subtle rounded-xl shadow-xl z-50\n```\n\nStructure:\n1. **Search input** — auto-focused on open, `placeholder=\"Search models...\"`\n2. **Patch error** — if set, a small `text-error text-xs` message below search input\n3. **Scrollable list** — `max-h-64 overflow-y-auto`, each row:\n   - `provider` in `text-text-dim` (dim) + `·` separator + `model-name` in normal weight\n   - Active model: `bg-brand/10 text-brand` highlight\n   - While PATCH in-flight for this row: spinner, list is `pointer-events-none`\n4. **Loading state** — single \"Loading…\" row while `listModels` is in-flight\n5. **Empty state** — \"No models found\" if filtered list is empty\n6. **Fetch error** — \"Unable to load models\" + Retry button if `listModels` fails\n\n### Model Name Display (Optimistic Update)\n\nThe displayed model name is `optimisticModel ?? modelName` (prop). On selection:\n\n1. `setOptimisticModel(selectedModelName)` — instant UI update\n2. `setPatchPending(true)`, `setPatchError(null)`\n3. `await patchAgentConfig(agentId, { model, provider })`\n4. **On success:** close popover, call `onModelChange()` to invalidate the agents query (server-confirmed refresh clears `optimisticModel`)\n5. **On failure:** `setOptimisticModel(null)` (reverts to original `modelName` prop), `setPatchError(\"Failed to update model\")`, popover stays open\n\n### Parent (`ChatPage`) wiring\n\n```tsx\n<ConnectionBar\n  ...existing props...\n  agentId={selectedAgentId!}\n  onModelChange={() => queryClient.invalidateQueries({ queryKey: [\"agents\", \"list\"] })}\n/>\n```\n\n---\n\n## Files Changed\n\n| File | Change |\n|------|--------|\n| `crates/librefang-api/dashboard/src/pages/ChatPage.tsx` | All changes: new props on `ConnectionBar`, model popover state + UI, optimistic update logic |\n\nNo backend changes required — `GET /api/models?available=true` and `PATCH /api/agents/{id}/config` already exist.\n\n---\n\n## Out of Scope\n\n- Showing model metadata (tier, context window) in the dropdown\n- Persisting model preferences across agents\n- Model switching from the Agents page detail modal (unchanged)\n",
